  "texts": [
    "To control the false discovery rate in multiple testing, we applied the Benjamini-Hochberg procedure to adjust all p-values, using an FDR level of 0.05 [37].To assess the presence of common method bias, Harman's single-factor test was conducted.",
    "The analysis revealed that four factors had eigenvalues greater than 1, with the first factor explaining 28.47% of the variance, which is below the critical threshold of 40% [38,39].",
    "This result suggests that common method bias is not a significant concern in this study.",
    "Furthermore, to mitigate the risk of multicollinearity, the primary variables were mean-centered.",
    "Centering involves subtracting the mean score of a variable from each individual score, thereby aligning the mean of the transformed variable with zero."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
